                <h1>Do Background Actors Get Paid? Here's What You Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Yes, background actors, often called extras, do get paid for their work in film and television. Their compensation can vary based on factors like experience, type of project, and location. Generally, union extras earn higher rates, while non-union actors may receive lower pay. Daily rates typically range from minimum wage to a few hundred dollars.</p>
